modules.description: This module implements a swap file system with operations to manage unnamed files backed by a block device. It provides functions to create empty files, append data, read partial content, and free allocated blocks, working with handles and a block device instance. Use cases include dynamic file storage on block devices with automatic or manual memory management.

This module implements a swap file system that manages unnamed files stored on a block device. It supports creating empty files, appending data, reading partial content, and freeing allocated blocks, using file handles and a block device instance. It is used for dynamic file storage on block devices with manual or automatic memory management.
